(gunshots)

612
01:49:02,354 --> 01:49:04,898
(gunshots)

613
01:49:09,069 --> 01:49:11,405
(gunshots continue)

614
01:49:21,665 --> 01:49:24,292
(man shouts in Spanish)

615
01:50:49,165 --> 01:50:51,251
¿ Tienes algo qué pedir?

616
01:51:35,126 --> 01:51:37,587
(officer shouts orders in Spanish)

617
01:51:42,674 --> 01:51:45,093
'Posición de tiro'

618
01:51:51,391 --> 01:51:53,727
'Preparen armas'

619
01:51:53,852 --> 01:51:55,770
(gun barrels click)

620
01:51:57,272 --> 01:51:58,607
'Apunten'

621
01:51:58,732 --> 01:52:00,817
(John) Duck you suckers!

622
01:52:31,679 --> 01:52:34,515
(rapid gunfire)

623
01:52:43,024 --> 01:52:45,109
(gunfire and shouting)

624
01:54:30,460 --> 01:54:32,712
(speaks Spanish)

625
01:54:37,675 --> 01:54:39,761
(continues in Spanish)

626
01:54:49,311 --> 01:54:52,606
'Preparen' 'Armas'

627
01:54:52,731 --> 01:54:54,816
(gun barrels click)

628
01:54:59,529 --> 01:55:00,989
'Apunten'

629
01:55:01,114 --> 01:55:02,366
'Fuego'

630
01:55:05,118 --> 01:55:07,204
(continues to shouts orders)

631
01:55:09,997 --> 01:55:12,083
(gunshots)

632
01:57:17,495 --> 01:57:20,039
But for the rich you sing.

633
01:57:34,177 --> 01:57:36,513
Oh Jesus Juan.

634
01:57:37,556 --> 01:57:39,641
(John laughs)

635
01:57:41,851 --> 01:57:47,274
Anyway if they ever get this thing under way
you might be able to...

636
01:57:47,399 --> 01:57:52,903
...might be make the border by what
some time tonight don't you think?

637
01:57:57,074 --> 01:58:01,287
America. It's America Juan!

638
01:58:02,288 --> 01:58:06,542
Oh Jesus if it's as great as they say it is

639
01:58:06,667 --> 01:58:09,086
filled bags stuffed full of dreams...

640
01:58:09,211 --> 01:58:11,171
Juan?

641
01:58:15,633 --> 01:58:18,303
Oh Jesus.

642
01:58:21,598 --> 01:58:24,142
Jesus Juan.

643
01:58:26,352 --> 01:58:29,981
What is it Juan and... John?

644
01:58:31,774 --> 01:58:34,611
Johnny and Johnny?

645
01:58:34,736 --> 01:58:39,114
I make the holes and you get in. 50-50 right?

646
01:58:39,239 --> 01:58:41,325
(clattering)

647
01:58:45,621 --> 01:58:47,706
(clanging)

648
01:59:01,469 --> 01:59:03,554
(agitated chatter)

649
01:59:05,765 --> 01:59:07,975
(siren blasts)

650
02:00:03,529 --> 02:00:05,573
What's happening?

651
02:00:06,282 --> 02:00:09,409
Oh they're just moving the train around.

652
02:00:10,118 --> 02:00:12,537
Seems we'll be leaving shortly.

653
02:00:14,038 --> 02:00:17,250
The uniforms have loaded the last of their shit.

654
02:00:17,876 --> 02:00:19,627
(whistle blows)

655
02:00:32,973 --> 02:00:35,100
(train whistle blows)

656
02:00:42,149 --> 02:00:44,234
(squawks)

657
02:01:12,220 --> 02:01:14,472
(squawking persists)

658
02:01:25,190 --> 02:01:27,275
(chicken clucks softly)

659
02:01:34,616 --> 02:01:36,701
(squawking recommences)

660
02:01:38,787 --> 02:01:41,080
(intense squawk)

661
02:01:41,205 --> 02:01:43,290
(silence)

662
02:01:51,340 --> 02:01:53,425
(train whistle blows)

663
02:02:03,685 --> 02:02:05,770
(crashing)

664
02:02:17,323 --> 02:02:19,534
(rapid gunfire)

665
02:03:16,504 --> 02:03:19,257
Get out of the way.

666
02:03:28,099 --> 02:03:31,520
What do you want from me you scum?

667
02:03:31,645 --> 02:03:33,522
Let me by.

668
02:04:03,258 --> 02:04:05,385
(gunfire continues outside)

669
02:04:28,490 --> 02:04:32,327
(noise of gunfire intensifies)

670
02:05:22,667 --> 02:05:24,961
It's yours.

671
02:05:28,506 --> 02:05:31,550
There's a fortune inside.

672
02:05:36,430 --> 02:05:38,390
...pearls.

673
02:07:25,619 --> 02:07:28,204
(man shouts) 'Jóvenes a México'

674
02:07:56,231 --> 02:08:00,276
Well this will not be going to America.

675
02:08:00,401 --> 02:08:03,488
(Juan) Maybe the train won't but we will.

676
02:08:16,750 --> 02:08:18,961
Hey...

677
02:08:20,838 --> 02:08:22,965
Which way is America?

678
02:08:27,636 --> 02:08:32,474
Well it's sure as hell not that way.
That's the way.

679
02:08:36,561 --> 02:08:39,063
Well then...

680
02:08:45,194 --> 02:08:47,280
...let's go.

681
02:08:48,406 --> 02:08:50,491
(both laugh)

682
02:08:57,248 --> 02:08:59,332
(cheering)

683
02:09:05,213 --> 02:09:08,175
Even Pancho Villa's heard much about you.

684
02:09:08,300 --> 02:09:11,970
He's always saying
"I want to meet this Miranda."

685
02:09:16,057 --> 02:09:18,143
Me?

686
02:09:19,394 --> 02:09:21,687
That's right.

687
02:09:21,812 --> 02:09:25,816
The military junta commander
told us everything that you've done.

688
02:09:25,941 --> 02:09:29,570
Whatever you heard I assure you
they were only words.

689
02:09:30,613 --> 02:09:34,950
Words cannot describe
what Juan has done and suffered for the cause.

690
02:09:35,075 --> 02:09:36,952
(Juan laughs)

691
02:09:37,620 --> 02:09:40,080
Hey doctor.

692
02:09:41,749 --> 02:09:44,126
How you been eh?

693
02:09:44,876 --> 02:09:48,296
This is a man who should talk to Villa.

694
02:09:49,672 --> 02:09:52,258
Hey.

695
02:09:54,844 --> 02:09:56,930
John.

696
02:10:06,523 --> 02:10:08,941
We thought we'd lost you doctor.

697
02:10:11,860 --> 02:10:14,238
(wheels screech)

698
02:10:22,746 --> 02:10:24,832
(crashing)

699
02:10:26,458 --> 02:10:28,836
Have you got a light?

700
02:10:32,922 --> 02:10:37,969
Listen Gunther Ruiz is after us
and Villa wants to talk to me.

701
02:10:38,094 --> 02:10:40,471
We should get outta here.

702
02:10:41,681 --> 02:10:48,020
Jesus Juan you can't leave now.
You're a glorious hero of the revolution.

703
02:10:48,145 --> 02:10:49,897
Can I tell you something?

704
02:10:50,022 --> 02:10:52,108
Fuck you!

705
02:10:57,362 --> 02:10:59,739
That's all.

706
02:11:13,420 --> 02:11:18,757
A military train carrying over 1000 soldiers and
heavy weapons is heading straight towards us.

707
02:11:18,883 --> 02:11:21,510
What about Villa's troops?

708
02:11:21,635 --> 02:11:26,891
He met resistance in the Sierra
and ask s us to hold out for 24 hours.

709
02:11:35,983 --> 02:11:39,028
- Where the hell are we?
- Approximately here.

710
02:11:40,528 --> 02:11:43,448
Ah it's a beautiful desert there.

711
02:11:43,573 --> 02:11:46,409
Not a stream or a canyon in 100 miles.

712
02:11:46,534 --> 02:11:51,581
- How long you think it'll take them to get here?
- Three hours more or less.

713
02:11:51,706 --> 02:11:53,708
Three hours.

714
02:12:06,720 --> 02:12:11,892
Well it look s as though
we'll have to stop 'em right here doesn't it?

715
02:12:13,519 --> 02:12:17,064
All that takes
is unbolting a couple of yards of track.

716
02:12:17,189 --> 02:12:20,442
But then what? They'd still slaughter us.

717
02:12:20,567 --> 02:12:21,944
Wait.

718
02:12:22,069 --> 02:12:25,197
There's more than one way to stop a train.

719
02:12:26,739 --> 02:12:30,451
- How much dynamite have we?
- Maybe 200 Ibs.

720
02:12:30,576 --> 02:12:33,037
Is that enough for you?

721
02:12:34,372 --> 02:12:37,416
Oh yes. It'll have to do all right.

722
02:12:38,125 --> 02:12:43,130
- But I also need a locomotive and a man.
- Sí sí sí OK.

723
02:12:45,216 --> 02:12:46,968
OK.

724
02:12:47,093 --> 02:12:53,223
- Someone who's brave and loyal to the cause.
- Never mind that. What do I have to do?

725
02:12:55,225 --> 02:12:57,227
Someone like Dr Villega.

726
02:13:04,067 --> 02:13:06,778
Well...

727
02:13:07,988 --> 02:13:12,658
- I... I'm honoured.
- (John) I don't doubt it doctor.

728
02:13:13,659 --> 02:13:18,164
Also because an old friend of ours
is in command of that train.

729
02:13:18,289 --> 02:13:20,416
A Colonel Gunther Ruiz.

730
02:13:28,924 --> 02:13:31,594
(train whistle blows)

731
02:14:30,274 --> 02:14:34,904
(John) Let's get shovelling man.
We'll never get up enough pressure that way.

732
02:14:49,125 --> 02:14:52,462
Come on put your back in it Villega.

733
02:15:01,179 --> 02:15:05,892
Let's stop pretending right away.
You know everything don't you?

734
02:15:06,017 --> 02:15:10,813
- You sensed it or guessed it.
- Simpler than that Villega.

735
02:15:10,938 --> 02:15:14,775
I saw you that night in the rain.

736
02:15:25,161 --> 02:15:29,498
I see.
You've already judged and condemned me.

737
02:15:39,674 --> 02:15:43,678
That's why you brought me with you. To kill me.

738
02:15:44,762 --> 02:15:48,683
It's easy to judge. Have you ever been tortured?

739
02:15:48,808 --> 02:15:53,688
Are you sure you wouldn't talk?
I was sure. And yet I talked.

740
02:15:54,980 --> 02:15:59,943
Some men died because of me.
What should I do? Kill myself? Why?

741
02:16:00,068 --> 02:16:03,155
The dead remain dead but I have not changed.

742
02:16:03,280 --> 02:16:07,993
I still believe in the same things.
I can still serve the cause.

743
02:16:08,118 --> 02:16:11,246
Shut up Villega! Shut up for Christ's sake.

744
02:18:21,913 --> 02:18:28,336
When I started using dynamite
I believed in many things. All of it!

745
02:18:30,129 --> 02:18:32,590
Finally I believe only in dynamite.

746
02:18:33,633 --> 02:18:35,717
I don't judge you Villega.

747
02:18:38,428 --> 02:18:41,723
I did that only once in my life.

748
02:18:43,016 --> 02:18:45,352
Get shovelling!

749
02:20:21,652 --> 02:20:24,530
(John) The end of the line Villega.

750
02:20:27,241 --> 02:20:29,619
And I can't help you now.

751
02:20:44,591 --> 02:20:47,636
Just close your eyes and jump.

752
02:21:16,080 --> 02:21:18,873
'Dios mío frena'

753
02:21:18,998 --> 02:21:21,459
(screechging)

754
02:21:22,335 --> 02:21:24,420
(whistle blows)

755
02:23:10,189 --> 02:23:12,273
(gunfire and explosions)

756
02:23:44,471 --> 02:23:46,557
(explosion)

757
02:24:32,184 --> 02:24:34,269
(gunfire continues)

758
02:25:01,754 --> 02:25:03,839
(piercing gunshot)

759
02:25:05,674 --> 02:25:07,467
(second gunshot)

760
02:25:08,218 --> 02:25:10,178
Oh shit...

761
02:25:13,681 --> 02:25:15,725
God...

762
02:25:57,140 --> 02:25:58,724
(groans)

763
02:26:35,427 --> 02:26:37,471
Hey.

764
02:26:37,596 --> 02:26:41,015
Man remember huh?

765
02:26:43,017 --> 02:26:45,769
You remember what you told me huh?

766
02:26:46,437 --> 02:26:49,231
You told me about America.

767
02:26:49,940 --> 02:26:54,320
And the bank s and the gold.

768
02:26:54,445 --> 02:26:58,073
Like you told me on the train remember?

769
02:27:02,453 --> 02:27:04,704
Hey hey.

770
02:27:06,122 --> 02:27:08,500
Hey.

771
02:27:08,625 --> 02:27:09,834
(Juan laughs)

772
02:27:09,959 --> 02:27:15,799
No you son of a bitch. Come on
you son of a bitch. You know you told me that.

773
02:27:15,924 --> 02:27:20,345
You leave me now
what the fuck is gonna happen to me?

